These instructions are to setup your development environment. Things which are required to be downloaded are in '''BOLD'''.
        
You need the following binaries which can be found at [http://pythonmac.org/packages/py25-fat/index.html here]
        
* '''Python''' (the Python which ships with Mac OS X is horribly broken) - [http://pythonmac.org/packages/py25-fat/dmg/python-2.5-macosx.dmg here]
        
* '''Numeric''' (for stable tpclient-pywx version) - [http://pythonmac.org/packages/py25-fat/dmg/Numeric-24.2-py2.5-macosx10.4.dmg here]
        
* '''numpy''' (for development tpclient-pywx version) - [http://pythonmac.org/packages/py25-fat/mpkg/numpy-1.0.3-py2.5-macosx10.4.mpkg.zip here]
        
* '''PIL''' - [http://pythonmac.org/packages/py25-fat/dmg/PIL-1.1.6-py2.5-macosx10.4-2007-05-18.dmg here]
        
* '''wxPython''' - [http://pythonmac.org/packages/py25-fat/dmg/wxPython2.8-osx-unicode-2.8.3.0-universal10.4-py2.5.dmg here]

* PyGame (for development tpclient-pywx version) - [http://???/ none known]

* pybonjour (for development tpclient-pywx version) - [http://o2s.csail.mit.edu/o2s-wiki/pybonjour here]

* py2app (for creating packages)  - [http://svn.pythonmac.org/py2app/py2app/trunk/doc/index.html here]

You will then need to install "cogito" ([http://www.dpompa.com/git-1.5.2.2.dmg here]) and run the following

(For stable)
<pre>
cg-clone git://git.thousandparsec.net/git/scratchpad.git
cg-clone git://git.thousandparsec.net/git/libtpproto-py.git
cg-clone git://git.thousandparsec.net/git/libtpclient-py.git
cg-clone git://git.thousandparsec.net/git/tpclient-pywx.git

# Setup various links
cd scratchpad
./setup.sh
cd ..

# Check all the requirements are satisified
cd tpclient-pywx
pythonw requirements.py

# Now run the client!
pythonw tpclient-pywx
</pre>

(For development)
<pre>
cg-clone git://git.thousandparsec.net/git/scratchpad.git
cg-clone git://git.thousandparsec.net/git/libtpproto-py.git
cg-clone git://git.thousandparsec.net/git/libtpclient-py.git#development libtpclient-py-dev
cg-clone git://git.thousandparsec.net/git/tpclient-pywx.git#development tpclient-pywx-dev

# Setup various links
cd scratchpad
./setup.sh
cd ..

# Check all the requirements are satisified
cd tpclient-pywx
pythonw requirements.py

# Now run the client!
pythonw tpclient-pywx
</pre>

